00:07:46.120 --> 00:07:47.410
Kind of bottom of the heap?

00:07:47.410 --> 00:07:52.251
&gt;&gt;Mark: The good thing about the TV animation,
was you're turning around, you're doin' half

00:07:52.251 --> 00:07:55.330
an hour episodes in like eight weeks.

00:07:55.330 --> 00:07:59.630
So I have to story board a half an hour of
stuff in eight weeks.

00:07:59.630 --> 00:08:00.630
So.

00:08:00.630 --> 00:08:01.840
And you don't get to redo it.

00:08:01.840 --> 00:08:06.780
You kinda do it and it goes off to Korea or
Japan to be animated and that's that.

00:08:06.780 --> 00:08:08.580
And then it airs on TV.

00:08:08.580 --> 00:08:11.960
So I did five episodes for "the New Adventures
of Johnny Quest."

00:08:11.960 --> 00:08:16.470
Which is a great learning process because
you're just doin' it from your gut.

00:08:16.470 --> 00:08:21.361
And then Warner Brothers' animation started
up because DreamWorks started up and it was

00:08:21.361 --> 00:08:22.361
being successful.

00:08:22.361 --> 00:08:26.600
So now everybody in Hollywood, all the studios
wanted their own animation business.

00:08:26.600 --> 00:08:28.680
And they still kinda do.

00:08:28.680 --> 00:08:38.300
So, I met a bunch of great people at Disney
who left Disney to start over at Warner Brothers.

00:08:38.300 --> 00:08:40.210
Bill Perkins is one of them.

00:08:40.210 --> 00:08:44.340
He was the art director on "Aladdin" and he's
fantastic.

00:08:44.340 --> 00:08:47.210
So I got to know him with my friends who were
working at Disney.

00:08:47.210 --> 00:08:50.000
You know, of the internship.

00:08:50.000 --> 00:08:52.750
And he went over to Warner Brothers and called
me and my brother.

00:08:52.750 --> 00:08:54.190
And says "Come on over here, guys.

00:08:54.190 --> 00:08:56.740
This is going to be wildly different."

00:08:56.740 --> 00:09:03.570
So we went over there and got hired with Warner
Brothers and then started doing "Quest for

00:09:03.570 --> 00:09:05.960
Camelot" which nobody ever saw.

00:09:05.960 --> 00:09:06.960
So don't.

00:09:06.960 --> 00:09:09.230
And then "Iron Giant" with Brad Bird.

00:09:09.230 --> 00:09:11.970
And that's when I met Brad Bird for the first
time.

00:09:11.970 --> 00:09:19.340
And then I stayed to do, I was head of story
on "Osmosis Jones."

00:09:19.340 --> 00:09:23.800
And then I got called to work on the first
"Spiderman" movie with Sam Raimi.

00:09:23.800 --> 00:09:24.800
&gt;&gt;Male Presenter: Wow.

00:09:24.800 --> 00:09:25.990
&gt;&gt;Mark: And so I went into live-action storyboarding.

00:09:25.990 --> 00:09:27.130
&gt;&gt;Male Presenter: What was that connection?

00:09:27.130 --> 00:09:28.130
